			 Performance best practices and configuration guidelines for SQL Server 2017 on Linux 

					 
								 09/14/2017 
							 4 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO:   SQL Server (Linux only) Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse Parallel Data Warehouse  This article provides best practices and recommendations to maximize performance for database applications that connect to SQL Server on Linux. These recommendations are specific to running on the Linux platform. All normal SQL Server recommendations, such as index design, still apply. 
 The following guidelines contain recommendations for configuring both SQL Server and the Linux operating system. 
